    "response": "To compute the **sample standard deviation** of the data set:\n\n$$\n\\{1, 12, -17, -3, -11, -5\\}\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 1: Compute the sample mean ($\\bar{x}$)\n\n$$\n\\bar{x} = \\frac{1 + 12 + (-17) + (-3) + (-11) + (-5)}{6}\n$$\n\n$$\n\\bar{x} = \\frac{1 + 12 - 17 - 3 - 11 - 5}{6} = \\frac{-19}{6} \\approx -3.1667\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 2: Compute the squared deviations from the mean\n\n$$\n\\begin{align*}\n(1 - (-3.1667))^2 &= (4.1667)^2 \\approx 17.3611 \\\\\n(12 - (-3.1667))^2 &= (15.1667)^2 \\approx 229.8611 \\\\\n(-17 - (-3.1667))^2 &= (-13.8333)^2 \\approx 191.3333 \\\\\n(-3 - (-3.1667))^2 &= (0.1667)^2 \\approx 0.0278 \\\\\n(-11 - (-3.1667))^2 &= (-7.8333)^2 \\approx 61.3333 \\\\\n(-5 - (-3.1667))^2 &= (-1.8333)^2 \\approx 3.3611 \\\\\n\\end{align*}\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 3: Sum the squared deviations\n\n$$\n\\text{Sum of squared deviations} = 17.3611 + 229.8611 + 191.3333 + 0.0278 + 61.3333 + 3.3611 \\approx 492.23\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 4: Divide by $n - 1$ (degrees of freedom for sample)\n\n$$\n\\text{Variance} = \\frac{492.23}{6 - 1}"
}